It looks like, although Eucalyptus does lack some headers that EC2 provides, this was really a python issue and has been fixed.  I tested with Eucalyptus 3.1 and a Precise guest:

{noformat}
$ python2.7 testcase.py 
attempting http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/instance-id with timeout=2
Looks good
